<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_FEATURE_DATA_D3D12_OPTIONS4">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates the level of support for 64KB-aligned MSAA textures, cross-API sharing, and native 16-bit shader operations.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_FEATURE_DATA_D3D12_OPTIONS4.MSAA64KBAlignedTextureSupported">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/winprog/windows-data-types">BOOL</a></b></para>
      <para>Indicates whether 64KB-aligned MSAA textures are supported.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_FEATURE_DATA_D3D12_OPTIONS4.SharedResourceCompatibilityTier">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><see cref="D3D12_SHARED_RESOURCE_COMPATIBILITY_TIER" /></b></para>
      <para>Indicates the tier of cross-API sharing support.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_FEATURE_DATA_D3D12_OPTIONS4.Native16BitShaderOpsSupported">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/winprog/windows-data-types">BOOL</a></b></para>
      <para>Indicates native 16-bit shader operations are supported. These operations require shader model 6_2. For more information, see the <a href="https://github.com/microsoft/directxshadercompiler/wiki/16-bit-scalar-types">16-Bit Scalar Types</a> HLSL reference.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>